Here is a 260+ line HTML-only prototype for a project titled "CodeTrack" (a basic front-end layout for a Source Code Management system). It includes structured sections like repository management, commit history, and code viewer UI components.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>CodeTrack - Source Code Management</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
    }

    header {
      background-color: #24292e;
      color: white;
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    nav {
      background-color: #0366d6;
      padding: 1rem;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-around;
    }

    nav a {
      color: white;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: bold;
    }

    .container {
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .section {
      background-color: white;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }

    .section h2 {
      color: #333;
    }

    .repo-list, .commit-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

   
